Nothing needs to be added to .gitignore since the only change is adding a markdown documentation file (.md), which is source content that should be tracked in version control.
# Examples 1:
(empty — output nothing)

# Example 2 (Project with artifacts):
# Compiled and build artifacts
*.pyc
__pycache__/
*.o
*.obj
dist/
build/
# Dependencies
.venv/
venv/
node_modules/
# Logs and temp files
*.log
*.tmp
*.swp
# Environment
.env
.env.local
.env.*
# Editors
.vscode/
.idea/

# Original rules preserved
*.log
